<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Overshine" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Overshine</orth> (cf. <emph>O'ershine</emph>), 1) to shine upon, to illumine: <cit><quote>o. the earth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 38</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to outshine, to excel in lustre: <bibl n="shak. tro 3.1.171" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 1, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.317" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 317</bibl>.
